# ============================================================
# TIMBER SUPPLY CHAINS & FORESTRY COMMODITY VOLUME
# ============================================================
# Where the Data Lives (Cloud Catalogs):
#   Google Earth Engine (GEE): COPERNICUS/S2_SR_HARMONIZED
#   (B8 Near-Infrared and B12 SWIR bands)
#
# Web GUI Tracking:
#   Copernicus Browser - Search Sentinel-2, use False Color
#   (Urban/Infrared) rendering to see cleared land.
#
# Geographic Testing Centers:
#   Vancouver Island Industrial Logging Forests (BC, Canada):
#     Bounding Box: [-126.2, 49.3, -125.1, 50.1]
#     — Track checkerboard clear-cutting patterns used by
#       commercial logging corporations.
#
#   Mato Grosso Forestry Frontiers (Amazon Rim, Brazil):
#     Bounding Box: [-56.0, -12.0, -54.0, -10.5]
#     — Monitors logging activity and land conversion.
#
#   Willamette Timber Production Zone (Oregon, USA):
#     Center: 44.310, -122.420
#
# Automation Strategy:
#   Intersect your calculations with the global open-source
#   Global Forest Watch data catalog to isolate active commercial
#   logging concessions.
#
# Example usage:
# vancouver_polygon = [[[-126.2, 49.3], [-125.1, 49.3], [-125.1, 50.1], [-126.2, 50.1]]]
